caption: I'm not a local but love love love this spot! I will definitely be coming back when I come down that way again. The drinks were fabulous and the menu is delectable. The tenders are awesome and the wait staff were proper.

Okay I have so many AMAZING things to say, so here’s my list:  1. They sat us outside and the patio was just amazing. Literally in love. It was the perfect atmosphere.  2. The service was great. Like some of the best service, especially in New Orleans, that I’ve ever had. They were pretty busy even tho it was only 7ish and our waitress still took her time with every table and was super personable without taking too long with anything! She was so nice and very knowledgeable of the menu.  3. The. Food. I got the Cochon de Lait Cuban sandwich and it was one of the best things I have ever put in my mouth! And I’m a total foodie, so I’ve had some good food. My boyfriend got the Andouille crusted chicken sandwich which was so good too. For our app, we got the Cajun fries with the comeback sauce and idk what they did to these regular old French fries but it was just perfect, especially with the sauce.  4. The prices. We were shopping for furniture all day and I was looking up places to eat and we just decided to go there last minute. We weren’t looking for anything super fancy or expensive, but when we got there, we were like oops let’s be prepared to pay a lot. But they had options for anyone and everyone. They had the ambience, service, and quality of food, for a super nice and expensive experience, but there were price options on the menu for just a casual, list minute dinner, which even if I am out for an expensive, thought out dinner, I still like to see those options!  Overall, it was amazing, if you’re reading this and you’re debating on going, go. I wish I lived in New Orleans so I could go more often!
This place was so fun! Was here for burlesque brunch on Sunday and the performances were great and the bar tenders Hunter and Michael were phenomenal. 10/10 will come back.
Absolutely a must when you’re in NOLA! Beer on draft at the table and the bread pudding is to die for. I will definitely be back!
Great drinks and food, cool bar area.

This was amazing! Chef Halliburton and his team are amazing. We first were introduced to this exquisite Seafood Gumbo by Dr. Gumbos food tour. We made a reservation and came back our last night in the French quarter. Are we glad we did. Of course I got more Gumbo. My wife got the Cajun fries with the comback sauce. It will make you comeback.  My wife got the Surf and Turf and I got the Duck Duet. My wife's conche de lait was perfectly smoked. The taste lingered in my mouth all the way until the next bite. I wanted more, but I had duck. His duck was cooked perfectly. They gave me a knife but who needs it. It was fall off the bone tender. I am not sure how he made his cassis reduction, but my wife who hates duck usually, said, "I don't know what he did with this duck and that sauce, but he needs to keep doing this. That is how you make duck!"  I thought we were done, but nope, we ordered the pecan not pecan pie with the peanut butter whipped topping. I love Reese's to the point where almost any peanut butter and chocolate tasting dish or treat never compares. This had me wishing I ordered it twice.  This was a fantastic night with plenty of good scenery and of course the out of this world dinner.
Nice environment and it’s so convenient just on the ground floor of the hotel!
Exceptional experience and service!

I walked past this place a few times a day really wanted to try it as their interior design looked good and intriguing. The ambiance is really nice. The food not so great, and too greasy for my liking. We tried everything on the sharable menu and got an entree and I did not love it. Cocktails were nice and service was great.

Great food and drinks! It looks very high end but there's no dress code so you can feel free to walk in.  We came especially because of the Yellow fine tuna sashimi cones.  They were very yummy, but I think I would've prefered it parfait style.  The Cajun gumbo was fantastic!
Perfect anniversary dinner. The staff was amazing and they gave us a card and a glass of champagne by the house. Perfect place to celebrate.  Decoration is stunning 😍
Excellent!  Wait staff was great and highly knowledgeable. Great food, better drinks and  New Years eve there was great. The ambiance is cool, clean and fresh. We will be back
Very good food. Very good service. Covid precautions were followed very carefully.
We came here as part of a food tour and had a great time! The gumbo was the best we have ever had. The chef was so friendly and picked out a wine to go with the meal that was absolutely amazing!
Some of the best craft bartenders in NOLA
Must go to if in Nola!
Best brunch. Highly recommend

Great bartender that took care of us in the morning. The food was tasty, though the seasoning on the potatoes was a little on the salty side. The cocktails were perfect to wash it all down with and enjoy a lazy morning in the quarter.
Good happy hour.  Taste good.
Service was excellent the place was amazing and the food wow
Food was tasty and presentation was artful. It's an expensive lunch and portions are on the small side. But it's an elevated experience from most other choices in the Quarter.

Had a fabulous time at the burlesque brunch while eating the most interesting brunch combination I've experienced in quite a while. The dishes were so flavorful, tender, and oysters fried to perfection! One of the best brunches in NOLA
Delicious.
Hunter was wonderful and gave us so many good recommendations!
Go for brunch Saturday or Sunday. Food and the show were great! We had crawfish tamale and surf & turf tacos...both excellent. The band and Bella Blue 👌. Bottomless mimosas (or Bellinis) worth it.

Really enjoy going to Sobou for their martini lunch! The Yellowfin Tuna cones are my favorite app. They change up the menu (maybe seasonally?) so you can expect to try new things. I find that I have a better experience when I sit at the bar rather than getting a table, the service is faster/better in general.
Nice cocktail bar.
Not enough of a variety

First time eating here and the food was very good. The only drawback was that there was a wedding reception in the back dining area, so the sitting for reservations was limited to an area that should be the waiting area for sittings. The ambience was very nice and we will return next time we're in the Big Easy.
Yum

Terrible brunch serivce and 18% mandatory gratuity for the large party, turned into a 2 hour brunch, never came around to refill bottomless drinks even once, and didn't even refill water glasses without being asked.  Also burlesque show was hardly as advertised.  Would've tipped 0% if we could've, absolute highway robbery. The food was good, but the service was bad enough not to warrant a 2nd star.  Update: they charged our credit card twice.. 🙃

The food was decent but the service was atrocious.  Never refilled water once in the two hours of waiting for our food...
Great soup.. corn and crawfish bisque a must try..
Fun place...good drinks

We come every Mardi Gras weekend for legs and eggs with Bella blue. It’s always a good time. Good food. Great service. Amazing food. Legendary Bella Blue burlesque and amazing trio of musicians.

Went here for dinner last night and loved the the decor of the place, very unique. Ordered a Moscow mule, very tasty. Had the Corn and Crab bisque and it was delicious. Took one bite of the Thai curried shrimp and was totally disappointed. The shrimp were overcooked, rubbery and I think what was meant to be rice was way undercooked and so very bland. No matter how much they tried to make that rice work was an epic fail.
Pleasant staff, nice cocktails, small but fun menu, good creole gumbo.
Fantastic choice of shoes.  Loved it
Delicious and inventive food and drink.
Excellent food and decent pricing Very impressed with their breakfast as well as their Sunday brunch. They do a burlesque show during the brunch and have live jazz music.
We had a lovely dinner experience.  The waitress was very nice and the food was delicious.  Great cocktails and the atmosphere was hip.

Not overly impressed with this place. The mirrors in the dining room were way cool.  The sushi yellow tail crudo was the best thing we had, along with the salad.  The ice cream cones with savory flavors was very neat, but not for a novice pallet. The ice cream was way left sweet and mixed with way right savory fish. See the deconstructed picture.  The mushroom caps were not cooked. Ok. The filling texture was a minced type puree and over salted.  The fajita meat was also over salted. The shrimp were good. The fajita sauce tasted like the same crystal hot sauce mayo that we had with the fried chicken on a stick. I like a flour tortilla not corn blended.  The chicken on a stick was unimpressive.  The gumbo roux seemed like either mix or corn starch based. The shrimp were over done and small. The rice was small and al dente for me.
Decent cocktails! Sit at the bar if you don't have a reservation. #keto option on the menu is the "eat healthy" seared fish!
Great entertainment and food. A must place to come to!

Let me start by saying if Sobou is in your plans, don’t make other plans because your night will consist of waiting to be served. Yes it is that bad. I could go on but this place already took enough of our time! You have all been warned!
Great atmosphere,  pretty good bar food.
The traditional gambo and the food is very tasty. Beautiful decor

Absolutely wonderful brunch! We came for the eggs and legs Burlesque brunch and couldn't have had a better time. The music and entertainment were great but the food was better. I had a Bloody Mary that was simple with a bit of heat and the surf and turf breakfast tacos. Definitely will stop in again next time I'm in town.

The service here is horrendous. My wife and I arrived a few minutes early for our reservation. I asked if it was ok. The hostess didn't speak, just rudely pointed us to a table. Then when my wife's $32 frittata came out, it seemed to be in bechamel sauce. Menu said melted brie, nothing about a sauce. When I tried to ask about it the server went to the menu and the FOH mgr came over and tried to tell me there was no bechamel. I asked if they could please check with the chef as this is an ALLERGY and was blown off. Then the prices on the check were $4-5 MORE compared to the menu. Very disappointed and will never eat here again!
Really nice burger and  classic seafood gumbo,  cool salads too

Do not go there for breakfast!! Even though the place was half empty, we waited 30 minutes to get our tepid water for our tea, did not get what we ordered, were not going to wait another 45 minutes for them to re-make it so ate a very mediocre continental breakfast. All of this with grumpy waitresses who obviously did not want to be working there.
Great food, prepared perfectly. Waiter could have been friendly and more attentive.
Didn't love it for Breakfast
Fun. Good ambiance.

My wife & I visited SoBou for the second time yesterday and they never cease to amaze. Customer service is on point and the wait staff is very professional.  We shared off of the reveillon menu and each course was delightful. The duck confit hash was probably my favorite. To top it off, they brought out a dessert (chocolate cheesecake?) with a sparkler for my wife's birthday. I should also mention, they are constantly playing the best music ever over the house speakers. SoBou is the place to be!
Great atmosphere,  wonderful food, and superb staff.

Burlesque brunch exceeded expectations.  We had the 2 course brunch and unlimited bellinis. The pork belly bahn mi was amazing—large portion size and so flavorful!  The duck leg also came with a savory/spicy seasoned rice. Would absolutely visit again the next time we visit NOLA.  The burlesque dancer was very engaging and an amazing spectacle. Service was great and I highly recommended it.   Sticker price of the 2 course meal brunch was higher than expected but totally worth it.  Go to Sobou!

We are visiting New Orleans with friends and went to SoBou for their burlesque brunch. I highly recommend this experience to visitors! Not only was the service and food exceptional, the burlesque show was so much fun! It was very playful and personal. I would absolutely come back. Additionally, the duck confit, gumbo, and bahn mi po boy were all delicious
I cannot begin to tell you how delicious everything is! We've eaten here several times and is always mmm mmm good!
Great Happy Hour appetizers and drinks.

Went here for happy hour and did not regret it. We had some of the bar bites and loved every single one! The drink prices were great for happy hour too! Definitely stop here.

Absolutely wonderful! If there was a 6 star option they would get it! DELICIOUS food with vegetarian options. We went duting the "Legs & Eggs" brunch. The band and performer(Bella Blue) we terrific!

Not recommended unless you want a lesson on how to not run a restaurant. The entire operation is so unorganized that drinks are wrong, everything takes forever, everyone is clueless, no one communicates from front of house to back. Truly an escapade of amateurs. I will say the food is tasty, but not even close to worth the cost

had the reveillon dinner. everything was great except for the dessert - cannoli was hard as a rock
Go to Legs and Eggs!
Went for a New Year’s eve dinner. Everything was amazing! Our seating location, the food, the party favors provided to us and the amazing cocktails. Will definitely recommend this place
Excellent food and atmosphere
Terrible service, we were waiting like 30 min to order, 30 more minutes to get the entree and 1h to get the main course. They wouldn’t take the empty dishes and they didn’t refill our water glasses.
Was recommended the brunch here but it was very disappointing. Bad service, mediocre food and very overpriced

Food was 5 star with fresh ingredients and great combinations. Service was not great, we sat at a table for over 20 minutes after check was dropped and it was never cleared.
Food was OK but not worth the price. The flavors were not amazing for the price we pay. Service was Ok. Pretty close to Bourbon Street and Frenchmen street.
Awesome service, delicious food, great drinks, terrific atmosphere.
Excellent seafood gumbo and I tried my first Sazerac.

We had taken a friend last Saturday night to Sobou for her bday dinner. The server Darrius and manager Maritsa were both wonderful, pleasant and rilled right along with our great time. I had some special requests for family coming in from out of town for Christmas Day. Maritsa made it all happen. Definitely made me feel like a King. Unfortunately the family members that were supposed to come into town for the Holidays had cancelled due to some health issues so I had to cancel these custom reservations, which was very painful to say the least. She put time into making the special request happen. Maritsa handled the conversation like a professional champ and said all the right things to the customer. From somebody who worked in the industry for 12 years, lives in the city, and runs multiple businesses now I can only say that I highly recommend Sobou, the atmosphere, the food, and the staff. The sweet potato beignets rocked too! I will be back with another apology for Maritsa. Merry Christmas.

The breakfast steak and eggs was amazing. The boudin style rice reminded me of childhood. I'm told the legs and eggs duck was similarly dreamy.  We were there for a special event on Saturday mornings, which was a ton of fun.

SoBou is a pleasantly designed bar attached to the W hotel.  The bar offers all the typical drinks you expect in New Orleans.  Bartender staff are very nice and make you feel at home.  It does not have the dive bar feel nor the history that you will find in others in the Quarter.  SoBou is more on the upscale side.  I enjoyed my drink and would return.
Excellent craft cocktails in a nice setting.  Highly recommend you go see the barkeep named Cynthia

Absolutely enticing! Stopped here for dinner for my first official day as a New Orleanian after a long relocation/move from Austin, TX, and if this is what I have to look forward to living here, I’m looking forward to it! The staff was on top of everything, had some great recommendations, and the food was delicious. I enjoyed getting a little dressed up, but was also relieved to feel like I was in a casual atmosphere. And you can’t go wrong with the food. I’ll be back!
Great food ...cool atmosphere ...really innovative.

The best bar in the French Quarter. Ask for Mike - he's friendly, accommodating, and has great drinks. Order the Rita Alexander and the Rustic Gumbo - you can't go wrong. Deb & Hunter were also so nice. Can't wait to come back to visit them!
Food was high quality well prepared, don't sleep on those potatoes

The bartenders are wonderful and very knowledgeable. They have a drag brunch and also 25 cent martinis with purchase of any lunch entree Monday through Friday. Lovely place
Wonderful lunch venue. One of the Quarter's classiest.

SoBou offers the most delicious, creative dishes I have ever encountered anywhere, including 29 years of living right here in the French Quarter. I could go on and on describing the amazing textures and flavors, from the tuna cones to the acorn squash to the seared gulf fish. EVERYTHING was fascinating and even fun. Just go taste and enjoy for yourself! Friendly, caring wait staff was an added plus. I wanted to personally compliment Chef Daren Porretto, but he was way too busy in the kitchen. Good sign!
The staff made my birthday feel so special and fun! I love the nice-hipster-trendy feel and all the food - and drinks - I had was delicious.

great atomosphere, excellent drinks, amazing seafood gumbo.  Manager plopped down next to us at the bar and opened her large laptop and started working and chatting with bartenders like there were no customers at the bar... odd and not a good business practice.

After having lunch with my family, I decided to try SoBou for some Thanksgiving food to go. Everything was wonderful. An interesting and unique Creole take on a turkey dinner! I read the menu, so I could identify everything :)  I only wish I had time to eat at the restaurant. The outside room was beautiful with all the bottles!

We made reservations for Thanksgiving, but we had a family emergency and stopped by to get food to go. It was absolutely the worst turkey and dressing I’ve ever had. The sweet potatoes were good but the dressing and mystery green mash were a mushy mess and inedible. We also ordered the rum cake and it was a huge disappointment. So much for a good southern creole Thanksgiving!
Unorganized with delayed service and out of food.
Fantastic Thanksgiving dinner. Awesome service!
Amazing happy hour deal lovely food!
Interesting, modern interior. Service friendly. Dishes both innovative (tuna/basil/avocado ice cream) and traditional (spicy Cajun gumbo). Good signature cocktails. I'd go back again.
High prices for average food and experience.
Very nice Happy Hour specials and drinks. Service was a bit slow.
The chicken and sausage gumbo is the best
Perfect for small plates alone or in a group. Modern cuisine, great presentation, and tasty drinks! I came here for my birthday and it was perfect. Good for young kids too!
Nice lunch at this interesting restaurant

The drinks are really good!
Great happy hour
Came here in a walking food tour. Really yummy samples
Can't stop thinking about the savory Biegnets & "the secret ingredient is"?
Everything about the restaurant was amazing; the staff, the food, the vibe... everything. This was such a great date night choice!
Excellent food. Service was a tad slow.
Awful customer service, food in small portions

Went for dinner, overall the experience was meh. The gumbo was amazing. Everything else was just mediocre. The sweet potato beignets were too sweet and didn’t have a great texture. The catfish tacos didn’t have a lot of flavor. The shrimp shortcake was ok but a little too salty. Overall it wasn’t really worth the price. The gumbo was the best we had on our trip though!
Amazingly fast service, tasty food and cocktails.
Great weekend happy hour. The Sazarac was delicious and Michael is a great bartender.
AWESOME Food and the servers were Outstanding!

This place is a trendy spot with a younger crowd. The atmosphere is very modern. Great vibes. The food is a fun spin on classic New Orleans cuisine. Our server was very attentive and the food was delicious.
Fresh delicious entrees and great entertainment. I had the gumbo and gulf fish for brunch, the fish was so fresh and cooked to flaky perfection.

On vacation from Ga. Read high reviews about this restaurants.  For someone who eats a healthy fitness diet. ...this place has nothing on the menu to stay in your macros . Was here black Friday for brunch. I wanted to try the beignet and rabbit since I'm in NO. Of course feeling like a fat a$$ leaving. Portions are very small. Lunch cost me and my bf$41. I got 2 small bits and he got braise ribs no drink. Lame. ! 1 star for we got front door parking Another star for ease of ordering and quick seating! Another star for quick delivery of food
Awesome, as always!
Great craft cocktails!

Went for brunch with a friend. We needed to sit at the bar because they weren't taking walk-ins. We still saw a little bit of the legs portion of legs and eggs. Bella is a very talented performer. The bartenders were friendly and great at making drinks. The food was fantastic.
Sobou's Eggs & Legs Brunch was amazing...their customer service was exceptional and their food divine! Our group quite enjoyed the burlesque!

The restaurant is located within the W hotel and comes with my highest of recommendation. To start, the aesthetics are well designed and the cleanliness factor is exceptional. The chef (well deserved title) maintains a menu that includes tapas as well as, full plate meals -that are most delicious. The SoBou changes up its design elements to include an area for conversation -which has a few tables with built in beer and wine taps, a nice bar with a television, an area with 8 to 10 tables at street level -which is bright and appears to be "tuned" for breakfast as well as, a dining area that is three steps elevated from the street which is designed with the use of intriguing lighting and a wall decoration that is based on infinity object visualization. The wait staff are both pleasant and knowledgeable and their "follow ups" are synchronized with the short pauses as the patrons eat their meals. Our favorite contributor was Joshua and at our last night of dining, the General Manager: Lelia stopped by to ensure our visit was at or better than our expectations.  My suggestion: Must visit!
Great happy hour menu! Excellent drinks and the best bartenders! Loved Brandy and Jared!

I have gotten better service at a closed McDonald's. Coffee arrived with no cream in sight until it was at absolute zero. And we had to ask the hostess for it! The "rotating burlesque show", well, there are three separate rooms. So we saw nothing most of our breakfast. And then, what did we see? See photo. Oh, also, half our table faced the wall. Who designs a place with a show such that half the audience faces a wall? And yet we still paid the same prices. If you can at all avoid coming here, so. Consider eating at a neighborhood dumpster, or picking up some chewed gum from the sidewalk instead.
Best happy hour in the French Quarter
Interesting and tasty dishes
Great food, management and staff. Atmosphere is swank/sexy. Great for date night!
Expensive but the food was goog

Ruined. Our. Evening. Party of 6: 3 had cold food, 2 had the wrong food. We were told the next round of drinks would be comp’ed by the server. The manager told us dessert was comp’ed. Bills come and both are still on the bills.  We’re so tired of sitting there for FOUR HOURS, we are just going to pay the bill anyway. After another 20 of our server disappearing with our cards, we find the manager and server decide to argue with us about the bill—EVEN THOUGH WE WERE PAYING THE WRONG BILL. Don’t waste your time here!
Really good food
Fantastic food and excellent service.
So feeaking good!
Good quality food for the price. The decor is upper end and the beverage menu seems to have something for all. I had the gumbo a d Poboy and they were very good. Good size portions.
Manager was awesome, service was awesome and the food killed it. Best food so far in our trip, congrats to the chef and staff.
good food, service is a little slow.  bartenders are sexy & personable.
Amazing food. Great service and ambience
Great bartenders!

Great friendly service. Food perfectly spaced between courses. Knowledgeable staff. Food well seasoned and cook. Great atmosphere.
Amazing brunch. The steak and eggs is so delicious. Wonderful music and burlesque show.

Closed at 10pm.... strange.
The whole experience was great!!!!
The food I was served was really good.
Another great Brennan family of restaurants. We enjoyed the food, staff and atmosphere.
Fantastic

Our server Brooke was great! She was super attentive and the staff was very friendly! She took excellent care of us and the manager Kelsie checked on us as well. It was my birthday dinner and they made it very special. Not to memtion the food was just excellent! We will definitely be back!

Drinks took forever,  it was 1 person a head of us, music was great and so was atmosphere but food was terrible, it tasted liked bad Chinese food and burnt gumbo, who wants to wait for expensive drinks with hardly any people around. I can go to the chart room.
username: The Gallery Salon & Spa New Orleans Lakeview

caption: I was here on a food tour, so only got a small taste of a few items from the menu. I enjoyed them very much and the restaurant seems like it has a nice atmosphere.
Don’t try to make a pick up order. They don’t answer the phone.
Very pleasant experience .
Great food and service.
Another masterpiece . The food represents the quality of Commanders Palace.
Customer service was good!
A must try if you are in the area.  Great food, atmosphere, & even better service!!
Delicious.
Had a great bartender (Hunter) and the drinks and food were amazing. Pretty good that the bar has easy access to the pool.
Awesome happy hour! Gumbo is great.
Craft cocktails, great happy hour food and location.  They also make the big ice cubes for your low ball drinks.    Bartenders have snappy attitude
Wonderful food and small bites
Had breakfast here several times during my stay.  Great food!
Pricey but very good food
Highly recommend the Burlesque Brunch. Very elegant presentation. Food was superve. Extremely creative rendition of traditional Creole cooking. Delicious original recipe cocktails.
The gumbo was incredible and the bread pudding was amazing. I would definitely plan on going again the next time I am in town.
Really good food and drinks! We ordered the shrimp dog appetizer, the blackened fish and the steak.
Stayed at W Hotel and had breakfast there daily. Pretty good food actually. Need a little variation on their daily menu tho.
I had an perfect experiment here. My waiter, Richard, was awesome and he's the reason that I'll be back when I teturn to New Orleans again.
The food and coffee was great!
Wonderful service and food

The food was good. The Shrimp & Crawfish beignets were great! The Street Surf & Turf tacos were well executed. We also had a very kind waitress in Toi. It feels like a little escape as well compared to some of the restaurants around the Square. Not the best food in NOLA, but definitely worth the price we paid!
Good food nice staff.

Went for breakfast on a weekday, but the amazing menu we saw online was not available. Server brought my husband a cup but no coffee. It took us almost ten minutes to get his attention to get some. Food came out fast, but frittata and fried chicken were overcooked and my friend's poached eggs were over hard. Waited 20 minutes for the check, which they were able to split, but they charged the wrong cards. We didn't feel like waiting to fix it. Wouldn't go back.
Not worth it for New Orleans
Great tasting food. Awesome ambience
Really good food and great service. The air conditioning was cracked fully which made the restaurant way to cold but otherwise a wonderful time.

I went to the Sunday Burlesque Brunch. The food and ambiance were fabulous; however, there were no Burlesque dancers or a Burlesque show that I saw. Very disappointing. It’s a great brunch, but not a Burlesque brunch.

Very very limited menu. I tried the duck which was alright. My buddy got the gumbo which was TINY. Not even close to a meal. We were comped our beers since the kitchen closed early and my friend couldn’t get more food.
One word, amazing!
This was the first stop on our walking food tour of the French Quarter. We had cracklins, crawfish beignets, and boudin balls. I would love to stop back in for a full meal.
Pricey but worth it. Awesome decor!

I picked this place without looking at the reviews. And honestly it was horrible. We sat at least 45 with no water even offered. Until (I'm guessing) the manager came over and asked if our order has been taken. Still took them about 15 min to bring out our water and juice. After we ordered (I ordered poached eggs) the food was really bad. The eggs were over cooked not poached and the sausage had a funny taste to it. The steak we ordered was over cooked and not medium rare as asked. The food was over priced and the service was bad. Will not recommend or come here again.

I had a craving for bread pudding the moment we set foot in New Orleans and this place did not disappoint. That bread pudding lollipop is great and so are the cocktails! The staff here was the best we encountered on our trip.

The worst customer service. The hostess ignored us for five minutes and no one came to take out order for another five, so we left. Food took forever the day before when we had breakfast. Fleur-de-lis across the street actually appreciates customers there...

On a Sunday night the service was so darn slow. It was not the server's fault. She was great but the food came out at a snails pace. We were there nearly 3 hours for dinner.  We ordered the prix fixe meal. The app was meh, the entree was good for me but not stellar and the dessert was not good. Miss this expensive and disappointing restaurant.
Skillfully made cocktails that are simply fantastic. Service at the bar is outstanding.
Great lunch special
Scrumptious food in an elegant setting, kind staff, in the heart of the French quarter.  Perfect!
Sit at the bar... Great bar service!

I had seen and heard of this restaurant for awhile since living in New Orleans. So glad to have finally visited it! Such a good experience. The food was more than delicious - it was an amazing experience!  The attention to detail and cleanliness was much appreciated.  The night began as we walked in and feasted our eyes upon the beautiful interior decoration of the walls.  We were seated quickly.  Erika was our waitress and she did a fantastic job!  She was efficient, friendly, observant, and had profound knowledge of the menu.  We started with the Small Bites and Cocktails.  The Soup Du Jour and the Gumbo Du Jour inspired us to try more from the Small Bites menu.  One delicious Small Bite led to another and before we knew it, we ordered 75% of the Small Bites menu.  If you’re looking for a unique gustatory delight, I highly recommend The Yellow Fin Tuna Cones. Take a small bite of the ice cream first to avoid brain freeze and then eat the rest.  I imagine it makes for a great palate cleanser prior to the Big Bites because of the citrus flavor from the pineapple ceviche and creaminess of the basil avocado ice cream - kinda like a sorbet.  Though, we never made it to the big bites because we were too full lol!  We tried a number of cocktails and found The Waiting Room as well as The Parakeet Nordine to be our personal favorites.  Even though we left with full tummies, we felt a little empty inside because of how attached we grew to the place in such a short time.  We can’t wait to return for the Big Bites, more cocktails, and dessert!  Thanks again SoBou and Erika for a great experience!

But it tasted like the brisket I've had at Mission BBQ, ie fast food brisket. It was decent, but definitely not worth the price I paid for it. The brisket was all piled on top of a sweet potato. This gave the whole dish an overpowering sweet flavor that detracted from the whole experience. A normal potato would've perhaps been better. Finally, the restaurant is quite dark. My parents both struggled to read the menu from the lack of available lighting, which the staff turned down even further while we were reading through the menu.  Recommendation: Maybe? Don't go there for a holiday meal, unless you really, really want to get mid quality food for higher prices. My co-workers and I went here as the reviews looked amazing. We sat down right around 8 p.m. just the three of us.. and it took an hour and 15 minutes for our food to come out. Not to mention the burger is literally just a slider... so it shouldn't have taken that long at all as we all ordered the same thing.  I'm giving it at least two stars though, our waitress was very understanding and even brought our table three shots on the house because of the wait.  then we asked about dessert and unfortunately the bread pudding was going to take 25 more minutes but she said she would check in the back and just heat it up if there was already one made. Luckily there was one made and it should only take 7 minutes... 15 minutes later we finally get it and it does not taste good. All in all I would say there are some very unique things on the menu and it has amazing flavor in the dishes but if you're there on a night where the kitchen might be short-handed... you can get very bad service in the terms of the wait time.  I also do not recommend the burger as it is way too small to be called a burger, it should be called a slider or not listed under the "Big plates" section of the menu.  Based on my experience I would never come back here again.  My positives would be that the drinks were phenomenal and our waitress was nice but getting there at 8 p.m. and not being able to leave until 10:20 is absolutely horrendous.

OhhhhOhhhh. So Bou. You almost had me at Hello, but unfortunately the waitress with the multi colored thirsty bob wig that was receding from her hair line sort of ruined for me- oh yes she did.  See there is thing that gets my nerves when dealing with people of color in the work place.  And before you jump crazy with assumptions I’m a chocolate morsel myself.  But getting back to my review- for some reason the line of being down to earth and professionalism is very hazy.  I don’t mind friendly, my God I love a sense of humor- but please - please don’t act as if I’m your ignorant cousin or little brother b/c that opens up a completely different layer of issues with me. I shouldn’t encounter issues where I am getting ready to dine.  Shall we continue to the story at hand.  I walked into So Bou and I was greeted with smiles and (WELCOME TO SO BOU) +++  We were seated where we requested ++  Let’s say this restaurant is beautiful, an absolute gem. There was no smudges or oily fingers, the tables were clean and it smelled very inviting. +++++++  So I was asked what would we like to drink- I prefer a cucumber with water (slices of cucumber with water) and I the waitress replied - eww you’re nasty, but I will fix whatever you would like.  Strike 1  Now So Bou dishes are very small when ordering the small bites, and when I say very small I mean 1 item small and as the waitress said - So Bou believes in quality not quantity. So Bou is like the ratchet version of Commander’s Palace.  Strike 2  You are never to refer to your establishment as ratchet anything especially when it looks like So Bou.  So I asked the hostess about certain dishes and the small bites fried chicken and she told me you only get one and that if I wanted more than I can order the chicken meal which is like $18 and it comes with 4 pieces and I just nodded my head like ok no problem and then these lovely words slipped out of that mouth of hers....  She said.. You know So Bou ain’t like Popeyes, this restaurant is a quality restaurant. You can’t get 4 pieces for $7.99.  When I tell you- I was 3 shakes from telling rainbow dull - what I really felt. Listen. There is nothing wrong with being yourself but monitor who you are b/c sometimes what you’re reaching for in others will come for you. But this is typical from what I have experienced in New Orleans from melanated people..  So moving forward I replied, I don’t eat at Popeyes - so I wouldn’t know.  Her comment was Strike 3.  Was the food good- yes - yes and yes! Instead of rice with gumbo they do it with mash potatoes. That’s a very interesting twist.  Was the waitress knowledgeable about the menu. Yes yes and yes.  Was she attentive and checked on us thoroughly. Yes indeed.  Would I visit So Bou again?  I most definitely will , but I will  not want her as a waitress.  Did she get tipped.. No.  I was insulted too many times.  Did I mentioned that I applauded her on the amount of cucumbers she had placed in my water. Then she mentioned, “oh that’s b/c I wouldn’t have to get anymore I can just keep refilling your glasses with water”.  I’m like mmmk thanks.  Would I recommend this restaurant to anyone else? Yes indeed. It’s beautiful- we just had the wrong waitress- that’s all.

***THERE WAS A RAT CRAWLING ACROSS THE DINING ROOM FLOOR AND THE MANAGER DID NOTHING***  The good food was RUINED by the service and management. After our final bite of food, a rat comes scampering across the dining room in front of our table to eat scraps discarded on the ground by a table nearby. When we urgently told our waitress, she blandly said “Oh... ew” and nonchalantly walked off (no rush) to get the manager. THEN, the manager finally comes over and doesn’t apologize — instead, he EXCUSES himself for this rodent.  He tells us, “Oh yeah, that little guy got in here yesterday and we couldn’t trap him.” WHAT?! EXCUSE ME?! You KNEW the rat was here ALL DAY YESTERDAY, you DIDN’T capture it, and you still allowed food to be prepared and served to customers?! Gross gross nasty YUCK.  The best part? They still MADE US PAY! The waitress dropped off the check, laughed nervously, and said “bye!” before quickly jetting off.  ***DO NOT GO HERE.*** There are plenty of good places in New Orleans that are CLEAN and under GOOD MANAGEMENT.

The food was awful and the service was worse! The waiter (older gentleman the night of  feb 24, 2018) honelsty could not have been more rude! Over- priced and  overwrought. My first time in Sobou was amazing.Such a warm atmosphere as soon as I walked in.My server was Kamryn Kelley, and she made sure I had a good night through the meal.She went above and beyond in making me feel welcomed.I had a great chat with the bartender Jared who took care of me and didn’t make me feel alone at all.Checked on me throughout! While the food was amazing, the service was horrible. We were ignored by the hostess for about 10 minutes when we walked in and that should have been our first clue how brunch would progress. It was 30 minutes before we saw our server after getting our table. We never once got water refills from our waiter, even after asking. After an hour and a half, we managed to get the attention of another waiter who took pity on us and refilled our quite dry water glasses. We got there at 110 and didn’t leave until 345. Most of that time was spent looking at an empty table and water glass. Several table were sat after us, had a three course meal, and left before we even got our main course. I normally cut places slack especially when they’re busy. However when we go there the restaurant was about half full and when we left we were one of three tables. In the entire place. Only two of those three belonged to our waiter. So unless you like unnecessary long neglectful waits with good food, I would not recommend Sobu.

The food at SoBou is SOOOO good. Maybe the best food I've ever had. I ordered a pulled pork on mash and it was delicious. We also ordered a Crabbed stuffed fish and it was gluten free and was, "the best thing I've ever eaten".  My only issue with this restaurant is that the wait time was very long. It took about an hour to get our food after we ordered and then about 45 minutes for desert. We ordered a mixed drink 3 times and it never came. I'm sure the waitstaff is busy but for the price you're paying, you kind of want your food to come out quicker and to get the drink you ordered...

I don't think it's her fault I think it's the fault of management here. Also arrived 15 minutes before my reservation and despite there being plenty of empty tables, including the one they eventually sat us at we were told our reservation was at 8 PM but we could wait in the bar. We took a stroll around the block instead. Pretentious without needing to be I think.
